# Git

## Principle

User commits. Model edits. Merge to main via consensus.

---

## Model Permissions

### MAY

- `git status`, `git diff`, `git log` — read-only
- `git add` — when user requests

### MUST NOT

- `git commit`, `git push`, `git merge`, `git rebase`

---

## Commit Format

```
type: description

Details if needed
```

Types: `test`, `code`, `refactor`, `fix`, `docs`, `rule`

---

## Branch Model

Current: working on `main`. Single branch.

### Planned (Phase 2+)

Three tiers: `main` (stable, RPi deploy), `dev` (developer + model), `agent` (RPi autonomous).

```
main
├── dev
└── agent
    ├── agent/skills
    └── agent/evolve-N
```

Flow: dev → consensus → main → agent pulls.
Merge to main: requires consensus of developers + model review.

---

## File Ownership

### Current

| Owner | Scope | Model may |
|-------|-------|-----------|
| Developer | `src/agent/core.py`, `src/cli.py`, `src/utils/` | Read-only |
| Developer | `.cursor/` | Read-only |
| Protected | `agent_rules/core-constitution.md` | NEVER modify |

### Planned (when modules created)

| Owner | Scope | Agent may |
|-------|-------|-----------|
| Agent | `src/skills/`, `src/agent/prompts/`, `src/agent/config/` | Full control |
| Agent | `tests/agent_tests/` | Full control |
| Agent | `agent_rules/runtime/` | Modify within bounds |
